The paper deals with the analysis of complex networks, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of Laplacian matrices and geometric embeddings suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on centrality measures and network robustness suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of alternative interpretations and empirical evaluations suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning).
